# Manual Test Cases – CRUD Testing

---

## CREATE TEST CASES

TC-CR-01 – Create a new task with valid alphanumeric text  
TC-CR-02 – Create multiple tasks with varied text and verify they appear correctly  
TC-CR-03 – Create a task with only whitespace characters and verify validation  
TC-CR-04 – Create a task with special characters (e.g., @, #, !, *)  
TC-CR-05 – Create a task exceeding the maximum character limit (e.g., more than 255 characters)  
TC-CR-06 – Attempt to create an empty task  
TC-CR-07 – Verify whether duplicate task names are allowed  
TC-CR-08 – Test rapid task creation in succession  
TC-CR-09 – Test task creation with Unicode characters  
TC-CR-10 – Verify task creation with malicious input (SQL injection, XSS)

---

## READ TEST CASES

TC-RD-01 – Verify the full To-Do List is displayed correctly  
TC-RD-02 – Verify all active tasks are displayed  
TC-RD-03 – Verify all completed tasks are displayed  
TC-RD-04 – Verify completed tasks remain visible under the correct filter  
TC-RD-05 – Verify newly created tasks appear instantly without refresh  
TC-RD-06 – Verify the count of pending items updates correctly  
TC-RD-07 – Verify placeholder text appears when the list is empty  
TC-RD-08 – Verify scrolling behavior with many tasks  
TC-RD-09 – Verify UI stability with a very large number of tasks  
TC-RD-10 – Verify no tasks appear under incorrect filter  
TC-RD-11 – Verify task persistence after page refresh  
TC-RD-12 – Verify accessibility features (e.g., screen reader compatibility)

---

## UPDATE TEST CASES

TC-UP-01 – Update an existing task name  
TC-UP-02 – Attempt to update a task with empty text  
TC-UP-03 – Update a task using only whitespace  
TC-UP-04 – Change task status from active to completed  
TC-UP-05 – Change task status from completed back to active  
TC-UP-06 – Verify updates reflect instantly without refresh  
TC-UP-07 – Apply and clear filters after editing  
TC-UP-08 – Edit task under filtered view  
TC-UP-09 – Verify double-click activates edit mode  
TC-UP-10 – Verify edited tasks maintain original order  
TC-UP-11 – Verify keyboard interaction (Enter to save)  
TC-UP-12 – Verify updates persist after refresh  
TC-UP-13 – Attempt to edit task using malicious code (XSS)

---

## DELETE TEST CASES

TC-DL-01 – Delete a single task  
TC-DL-02 – Delete multiple tasks one by one  
TC-DL-03 – Delete a completed task  
TC-DL-04 – Delete all tasks  
TC-DL-05 – Verify "Clear" button removes completed tasks only  
TC-DL-06 – Verify deleted tasks do not reappear after refresh  
TC-DL-07 – Rapid deletion testing  
TC-DL-08 – Verify "items left" count updates correctly  
TC-DL-09 – Verify bulk deletion behavior  

